description:
Featured in the App Store "Best New Apps".

"Whether it's for an Uber taxi, an AirBnB holiday or DICE gig tickets on your phone, the app age is here." - The Metro

“DICE will change the landscape of London’s music scene.” - London Evening Standard

"DICE aims to take tickets out of the hands of touts and put them into the phones of fans" - The Guardian

“The music industry needs disruption. Enter DICE.” - TechCrunch

“What you see is exactly what you'll pay, so when you do, you'll immediately be given an app-based e-ticket that will get you inside the venue with the minimum of fuss.” - Engadget



DICE is run by fans for fans. We handpick the best gigs in London and offer you the tickets with no booking fees. Trust us to find you incredible shows, no catch.

We can do this because we’re 100% mobile and have worked hard building great relationships with top artists, promoters, clubs and venues.

DICE is curated by some of the best music writers in the world. They listen to everything since life’s too short to send you to bad gigs.

Thanks to our great relationships with artists we often get the tickets no one else can. If a show is sold out then join our Waiting List. There’s a good chance we can get you in or we’ll talk to the artist about adding another show. 

Our team of data scientists are working hard to personalise DICE for you. The more you use it the smarter it becomes and the better the recommendations are. Our dream is to find you events you’ve never heard of and blow your mind. 

So download and get face-value tickets to Jack White, Little Dragon, The Black Keys, Metronomy, FKA Twigs, Biff Tannen or Basement Jaxx today. All these artists (and many more) have joined DICE from day one.

This is just the start.

releaseNotes: A big update that finally allows you to share events with whoever you like. We now have deeper than Barry White links from web to app, friendlier error messages (as opposed to borderline unfriendly), the hottest QR codes since 2009 and a slick new Facebook (some little SF start up - could be good) login.
